abstract: George Vecsey Sports of The Times column holds that New York Yankees pitcher A J Burnett's clutch performance to help propel the Yankees to victory over the Detroit Tigers and extend their playoff series is reminiscent of a similar scenario five years earlier.
snippet: Déjà vu was back, with the Yanks relying upon an unlikely starter, A. J. Burnett, to get them back to the Bronx. This Motor City game of chicken had not happened for all of five years.
lead_paragraph: Déjà vu was back, with the Yanks relying upon an unlikely starter, A. J. Burnett, to get them back to the Bronx. This Motor City game of chicken had not happened for all of five years.
